g.text: - What is the cause for the problem?
- Who are affected by the problem?
- How to replicate the problem? and How it happened?
- Gather information and get clarity on the goal.
- Cross verify the information for credibility.
- All required infomation should be present before
- Find limitations and capabilities with the context of
who/what is going to use the solution and
- Have we solved this problem before? Info on that.
- What are the ways to solve the problem? - Strategies
- Evaluate each strategy to reach the goal against
resouces required and time to solve it.
Amount of resources required for each type,
Estimated/calculated time to solve the problem and reach goal.
- Eliminate all strategies which cannot solve the problem with limitations.
level of acceptance of pros & cons of solution(descending) by requester,
- Discuss the top strategies with the request and finalise the solution.
- Build the minimal viable product with the finalized solution.
- Check if solution meets the expectations of requester.
- Check for issues and send for refinement.
- On acceptance of results, prepare documentation
- Describe the need to create a solution.
- Describe why and how we picked the solution.
- List type of inputs and its limitations.
- List the benefits of the solutions.
- List the limitations of the solution.
- Prepare important metrics which will help us
identify how good the solution works.
- Prepare a mechanism to monitor the metrics.
- Show the metrics in simple and comprehensible manner.
